`ConcurrentModificationException` means your logic is wrong - you are editing and iterating a map at the same time.

The iteration `numMap.keySet()` is the values of `nums` - you should be OK to change the outer loop to:

    for (int n : nums) {
        ...
    }

This avoids `ConcurrentModificationException` on the iterator while edits are performed. You don&#39;t need to use `ConcurrentHashMap` over `HashMap` - both should work fine in this situation, and the tests pass for 100,000.

