Let&#39;s say you have `rowNumber` defined like this:

    int rowNumber = 10;

and if you directly use the rowNumber in the XPath like this:

    driver.findElement(By.xpath(&quot;//table[@id=&#39;stock&#39;]/tbody/tr[rowNumber]/td[1]&quot;)).click();

the problem with this approach is, your xpath will look for `rowNumber` for tr tag. Just like see the `td[1]`. 

and `tr[rowNumber]` is invalid since the basic XPath expression is 

    //tagName[@attributeName=&#39;attributeValue&#39;]

so in order to parse the variable, we have to use `&#39;&quot; +var_name+ &quot;&#39;`


so something like this:

    driver.findElement(By.xpath(&quot;//table[@id=&#39;stock&#39;]/tbody/tr[&#39; &quot;+rowNumber+&quot; &#39;]/td[1]&quot;)).click();


should work

